e Latin personal name <i>Folius</i> (which is embodied in the common placename Fogliano)."]}]},{"name":"Bartholomew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of New Testament origin, the name of an apostle mentioned in all the synoptic gospels (Matthew, Mark, and Luke) and in the Acts of the Apostles. It is an Aramaic formation meaning ‘son of Talmai’, and has been assumed by many scholars to be a byname of the apostle   Nathaniel .  <i>Talmai</i> is a Hebrew name, said to mean ‘abounding in furrows’ (Numbers 13:22)."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":45,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":54,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Bartholomew Foliot was born in 1170, in Waterstock, Oxfordshire, England, his father, Bartholomew Foliot, was 22 and his mother, Cecily Bardolf, was 28. He married Beatrix de Bardolf in 1184, in Thame, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after 1252, in his hometown."},"et":{"1170–after 1252":"1170–pärast 1252","1170–1252":"1170–1252","1170–Female":"1170–Surnud","1185–1225":"1185–1225","1148–1175":"1148–1175","1142–Female":"1142–Surnud","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1148":"1148","116